  "body": "## Bug description\r\n\r\nIt should be possible to set the run-time log level in 2 ways:\r\n- `--log-level` CLI option\r\n- `STATUS_RUNTIME_LOG_LEVEL` environment variable\r\n\r\nThe switch kinda works, but with limitations.\r\n- In debug build: I'm not getting TRACE logs.\r\n- In release build: I'm not getting DEBUG and TRACE logs.\r\n\r\nAll other settings like ERROR, WARN, INFO always work.\r\n\r\nEven though I can see that the log level is set to correct value here:\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/blob/34d0719b397efba9e7b2ffbea541d5e748fcb67d/src/nim_status_client.nim#L63\r\n\r\nI still don't see desired log messages in the terminal.\r\n\r\n## `TRACE` level and status-go\r\n\r\nActually, if you try to set log level to `TRACE`, you won't be able to login to the account, because we pass this value to status-go, which doesn't support `TRACE` value. This should also be fixed, it's kinda related.\r\n\r\n## Possible reason\r\n\r\nThere're 2 places where we check if `LOG_LEVEL` env variable is set:\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/blob/34d0719b397efba9e7b2ffbea541d5e748fcb67d/src/app/boot/app_controller.nim#L441\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/blob/34d0719b397efba9e7b2ffbea541d5e748fcb67d/src/app/boot/app_controller.nim#L136\r\n\r\nThis is definitely wrong, at least because the env variable name is now `STATUS_RUNTIME_LOG_LEVEL`.\r\nAlso, we should check is `--log-level` CLI option was set.\r\n\r\nI tried to fix it, but it still didn't work for me üôÅ \r\n\r\n## My attempts\r\n\r\nI tried to fix it, you can find my attempts in `temp/runtime-log-level-fix-attempt` branch.",
